text: Ho Tze-Lok (, born 26 October 1995) is a Hong Kong professional squash player. As of February 2018, she was ranked number 48 and highest ranking was rank number 43. in the world. She has won the 2017 City of Greater Bendigo International, Perrier Challenge Cup and Brisbane City Sandgate Open. ==References== Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Hong Kong female squash players Category:Asian Games medalists in squash Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Hong Kong Category:Squash players at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games
